Brilliant, thank you.

David

Hi David,

Ok you are all set to you WP Rocket now. We have completed setting up the Kinsta cache.

Hi again Heath,

As we're using WP Rocket to speed up the website, is there something we need to do within Kinsta to make this work properly? Right now when activating WP Rocket I'm getting a notification about some kind of setting in Kinsta.

"Your installation seems to be missing core Kinsta files managing Cache clearing and CDN, which will prevent your Kinsta installation and WP Rocket from working correctly. Please get in touch with Kinsta support through your MyKinsta account to resolve this issue."



Cheers.

Thanks Heath - appreciate the speedy turnaround.

Kind regards.
David

Hi All, 

Just confirming the new version of your website is now on the live server.

Copy that, commencing the push.

The new site should be live shortly. I will confirm once complete.
Yes, please go ahead.

Brilliant, thanks Heath - looks good from my side. Patricia - I'm happy if you are?

David

Hi David, 

Can you please check now? I believe they have all been flushed out.

Hi Heath, looks like the new staging site is still pulling quite a lot of resources from the Studio 21 Staging website. Can you do a find-replace to fix that so it all pulls from the Kinsta please?

Cheers,
David

Hi David, 

Here is the link to staging: https://staging-phoenixdx.kinsta.cloud/

Please review and let me know if we are ok to push to live?
Thanks Heath.

Ok noted, thanks David. 

We will have this ready in approximately 1hr. We will transfer this to staging on our server for approval and then push to live. 

I'll keep you updated.

Perfect - if you could transfer the staging site to live that would be great.

Here is access to the staging site Heath:

Login: https://phoenixdx.studio21.dev/wp-admin
User: Heath
Pwd: lM%$SjhdG(N)zwY)eBR&a9p*

If you can let us know when it's transferred I'll jump in and reactivate all the paid plugins.

Thank you,
David

Hi David, 

Unfortunately not, that plugin is not allowed. 

We can migrate the site for you though, all would need is admin access to the new site, or a backup copy of it.

Hi Heath, that's great we don't have any of those plugins on the new site.

Are we able to activate All in One Migration?

David

Hi David, 

Apologies, I didn't check if it was on the banned list. 

We recommend this plugin for migrations:
https://wordpress.org/plugins/migrate-guru/ (I can provide the SFTP information if you would like to use this method). 

Also, the other banned plugins are:

  • all-in-one-wp-migration 
  • allow-php-execute 
  • backupbuddy 
  • backwpup 
  • better-wordpress-minify 
  • cache-enabler 
  • codistoconnect 
  • dynamic-widgets 
  • eww-image-optimizer 
  • exec-php 
  • inactive-user-deleter 
  • jch-optimize 
  • litespeed-cache 
  • login-wall
  • p3 
  • p3-profiler 
  • pagefrog 
  • rvg-optimize-database 
  • snapshot 
  • updraft 
  • updraftplus 
  • wonderm00ns-simple-facebook-open-graph-tags 
  • wordpress-gzip-compression 
  • wordpress-popular-posts 
  • wordpress-rss-multi-importer 
  • wp-db-backup
  • wp-db-backup-made
  • wp-optimize

Hi Heath, thanks for getting back to us so quickly.

If you can please un-ban and activate the migration plugin that would be great. Thank you.

Are you able to let me know what other plugins may also be banned just so we don't run into any issues with the migration please?

Cheers,
David

Hi Patrica, 

Sure, if you like you we can add this plugin: https://en-au.wordpress.org/plugins/all-in-one-wp-migration/ to you website for you. 

Or you can send us some admin logins to the new site and we can take care of the migration at our end.
